From James Azania, Lokoja No less than seven persons are said to be on compulsory self-isolation in Kogi State. The Kogi State Ministry of Health, on Tuesday, said the persons would be on self-isolation for the first 14 days under the strict monitoring of the ministry. This was captured on the Facebook wall of the Commissioner for Health Dr. Saka Audu who noted that the seven persons had visited the Covid-19 high risk countries in the last one month.  It added that Lokoja, the state capital has five persons, Ajaokuta and Okene LGAs with one apiece, so isolated. The commissioner enjoined any one that recently returned from any of the high risk countries to contact the ministry for necessary action to prevent the escalation of the virus. 